included.description: I created and established this program  to help refugee families with young children access food and health resources in their communities in order to provide food security during their resettlement period. The program involved developing culturally appropriate health education curriculum for children and pregnant women that included healthy eating, exercise, living healthfully with chronic disease, and maintaining holistic wellness. This program utilized supportive education in client homes to help establish strong and healthy eating habits, budgeting skills, and access to local resources.
included.title: Food Security Home Visit Program

included.name: Preparing the Body, Preparing the Mind: A Comprehensive Educational and Support Platform for Perioperative Patients
included.description: Providing patients with tools to increase self-efficacy and understanding of their own personal experience of health is crucial for a more positive healing journey after surgery. This paper introduces a solution to the lack of education and stress reduction support surrounding surgery by proposing a mobile application addressing pre- and post-surgery self-care through a holistic lens.  The content of the mobile app described at length in this paper includes modalities to address stress reduction for patients during the perioperative period.
